text: The Panamanian lawmakers thought they were going on a shopping spree, but ended up sparking a diplomatic row with China over Taiwan. Now they're debating whether to switch to using chopsticks or learning Mandarin for their next trip.
Carra: "Liverpool must sign in January, even after their summer spending spree? Did they run out of money at half-time?"
The experts say to avoid ultra-processed foods like that one time I ate a entire box of pizza rolls and had to call the pizza rolls hotline for assistance.
President Bush's eulogy for Dick Cheney: "I know everyone says he was a great hunter, but the truth is, the only animals in his life were the ones on the stock market."

The Mostert distraction is like having a comedian on the field - you can't help but laugh, but it's not the right time for laughter in South Africa's team. Why did Mostert bring a whistle to the cricket match? To call out the ducks when they were swimming across the pitch!
Troy the parrot says to his owner, "You're looking rather green today, have you scored a hat-trick of drinks?"

The Australian teens were so addicted to Instagram, they didn't notice their accounts were being closed until they tried posting a selfie and got a message saying "Sorry, you can't post that in Australia."
AI should be regulated by its creators, not the other way around. Why did the EU try to regulate AI? Because it couldn't program a decent set of rules itself!
The hotel was completely silent because it was run by professional sleepwalkers.
Bundee Aki is such a skilled player, he can make even a rugby ball laugh just by saying his own name.
My significant other says I should love her unconditionally. I told her that's impossible, but she still loves me sometimes.
Troy Parrott decided to take the classic Hero's Journey... he signed up for a marathon, hoping to score some goals and maybe snag a few assists along the way.
Gen Z are turning accounting into a flocking phenomenon, proving you can't handle numbers without Excel skills.

Glenn Close says Kim Kardashian's "All's Fair" reviews are "zero-star", but I bet Kim thought she could just walk into an Oscar ceremony and win best actress. At least Close has the acting skills to pull off a glare.
Fiber supplements are like vitamins, but instead of preventing illness, they promise to make you an Olympic runner.
The Brazilian host of COP30 is a slow runner and keeps stopping to check if his shoes match.
Oneohtrix Point Never's Tranquilizer review: I felt so relaxed, I accidentally reviewed it while surfing the web on my toaster.
Dr. Vallance and Sir Whitty decided to delay the lockdown. Dr. Vallance said, "I have a 99% chance of being right." Sir Whitty replied, "And I have a 50% chance of being wrong."
The players were so bad at Gaelic games, they couldn't even kick the ball out of the field, so they had to use a traditional Vietnamese method - the buffalo.
A meteorologist predicted rain, but instead he got his feet wet while playing soccer.

A goldfish from Ottawa says to another: "I heard they're going to euthanize us all because there are too many of us! " "Really? That's a relief," replies the other goldfish, "I was starting to think my tank was just really good at hiding me."

My significant other bought a parrot and named it "Jealousy" because now every time I flirt with a stranger, the bird screams "I do get jealous and question whether I’m cut out for non-monogamy!" at the top of its lungs.

A man named Tom was so thirsty he decided to drink from a well. Unfortunately, it was the world's deepest well and he had just set a new Guinness World Record for longest time spent trying to reach water.

The report said the UK's Covid response was "too little, too late" - I think they meant it as a compliment, but it came out more like "your response was so small it could only be seen with a microscope after the party had already crashed".
Commuters on the M7 are so stuck in traffic, they've started a petition to have a giant clock installed every mile to help them estimate how much longer they'll be 'trapped'.
The Prada heir's new role at Versace is to decide if they should sell more belts or handbags - because apparently, less is never enough.
Miriam Toews is so loud, she once walked into a quiet town and the mayor had to declare a noise pollution emergency.

Keira Knightley's husband must be a master at finding unique gifts, even if they are of less than desirable subjects. Why not give his collection a break and gift him some pictures of puppies instead?
The Ninja dual zone air fryer will be fighting for your dollars this Black Friday 2025, but don't let it trick you into thinking it's any better at stealth than a herd of elephants in a cornfield.
The house couldn't decide if they wanted to shame Cory Mills or throw a housewarming party for him.
Doctor asks a patient, "What's your favorite body part?" Patient replies, "My wallet. It's the only one that always has an open invitation to the doctor's office."
Nonalcoholic spirits are taking the world by storm because they're like the underdogs in a bar, constantly proving that they don't need a buzz to be the life of the party.
A trader tweeted his stock picks and now he only gets doge coin alerts.

Duvet day is officially a thing now, because apparently some parents are so tired of their kids missing school that they're letting them do it on purpose. Why did the teacher refuse to grant time off for a duvet day? Because she didn't want to set a dangerous precedent where students could just stay in bed all week!

The comet 3I/ATLAS decided to apply for a job at NASA, thinking they'd finally found its forever home. They were interviewed by an alien and asked, "Why should we hire you when you keep disappearing into space?" Comet 3I/ATLAS replied, "I promise I'll just do a flyby and not stick around!"
A pigeon walked into a bar, ordered a pint, and started sobbing about his late wife. The bartender said, "Another day, another cry, mate. But why the feathers?"
The polar bear was so excited for the polar vortex to arrive, he accidentally booked two nights.
AI is like a boss's secret ingredient in microwaved career advancement soup.

Alice Zaslavsky's recipe for garlic red peppers with a creamy white bean dip, AKA "papula" - because sometimes, when you're feeling down, all you need is a good dose of red peppers and a side of depression.
A real estate agent in California says: "I have never sold a house in my life. But I can promise you one thing: it will be the last time you buy a house in California."
David Muir had to interpret "paw-some" into ASL for the occasion.
The SA Reserve Bank just cut the repo rate, now my bond is a coupon-clipping clown car!
The astronauts on the satellite were worried about rising sea levels, but they were more concerned about their own sinking ship of beer cans.
The school was closed due to thundersnow, so the teacher had to teach her doggy weather-related tricks like "roll over and paws up".
A giant spider decided to host a web-building contest at the Greek-Albanian border cave, but when it came time for judging, the spider realized it had forgotten its measuring tape.
The captain has a tough job, but at least he doesn't have to deal with the endless pool parties and karaoke sessions.

A man went to buy a Black Friday deal for his wife, but ended up buying a chainsaw. When she saw it, she said "This is exactly what I needed!" and he replied, "I thought it was for you, but it says 'him' on the box."
A group of anagrams walked into a bar and asked for a cocktail made of the word 'listen'. The bartender said, "Sure, and I'll just call it'silent'."

The Klamath River decided to restore itself, but instead of just cleaning up, it went full salmon. Now everyone's trying to catch up. Why did the salmon cross the road? To get to the Klamath River's restoration meeting!
The Senate is a house of spies, but they can't afford the phone bills.
The team that qualified for the World Cup finally got their chance to play, and one player exclaimed, "Finally, I can show them why we're called the 'Soccers'!"

The Prince of Wales was asked about his children's feelings towards missing the Paddington bear at the Royal Variety Show, and he replied, "They were devastated, but at least they have each other and their own royal pandas."
The comet 3I/Atlas is so fast, even light can't keep up with it when it's going to the bathroom.
A painting that sold for millions? Must be a masterpiece of... price gouging!
Raking leaves is like nature's way of telling you to buy a leaf blower, but if you ignore the message, your allergies will thank you in the spring.
Owls can't escape their fate of being mixed into the batter. But at least this one is recovering in a state known for its delicious pies!
Chef Mamdani's win means his restaurant will now serve "win sauce" on the side.
The best VPNs I’ve used are reduced ahead of Black Friday because they finally realized they were just running in circles.
The best way to catch up on sleep is to have a slumber party with friends. Just make sure you bring a friend who snores like a chainsaw, because that way, you'll be counting sheep in no time.
The Korean coast guard said the helmsman was so engrossed in his phone he didn't even notice the ferry was running aground - until his fish told him "Hey, we're stuck!"
The US is so determined to prove its dominance that it's even expanding its Wi-Fi range into outer space, leaving Europe and Asia still searching for the password.
Lily Allen's new album is called "West End Girl" - I guess she finally found a place where she feels like a real person again after all those years of fame. Maybe she should try therapy instead.
The dice decided to take a holiday, leaving the craps table short-handed and many players in hot water.
Winter can be chilly, but with these tips, you'll be snoring like a bear in no time: "Make sure your pillow is fluffed up - it's like having a tiny down jacket under your head!"
Evolutionary biologists finally figured out why we can't stop kissing our partners during a pandemic: it's not a bug, it's a feature!

Anna Ansari's cookbook "Silk Roads" is filled with recipes from her travels, including one for a stew that combines every ingredient she couldn't finish at her hotel restaurants. It's called "Leftoversaremystaple."
In times of sweeping change, clarity matters most. But don't ask my husband for advice on changing anything, he's still trying to decide between a toaster and a coffee machine.
A picture of a person yawning with the caption "World News" is the funniest thing I've seen all week.
The stock market is like a game of roulette where Nvidia won the first spin, but then everyone kept betting against it, thinking it was rigged.

A Gustav Klimt painting just sold for a record amount... I wonder if it was worth it. After all, wasn't he the artist who painted a horse's bottom in gold and called it "The Woman in Gold"? And now we're supposed to believe it's worth more than the Eiffel Tower?
Millennials are leaving college and entering the real world, only to find their parents' old vinyl records, VHS tapes, and a never-ending supply of Advil in their inheritances.
The draw for the World Cup 2026 playoffs was like a game of musical chairs, but instead of music stopping, it was whenever someone said "goal!"
The judge asked the defendant if he had any final words, to which he replied, "Your honor, I didn't do it because I have excellent alternative facts."
The company's success is so overwhelming, even their printers are now producing money instead of documents.

Millennials are tired of being bossed around, so they're just becoming conscious unbosses and letting each other figure it out. Now their meetings consist of everyone staring at the floor while muttering "I feel responsible for this."
Abbott's new acquisition is so powerful, it can detect if you've left the toilet seat up.

George W. Bush is still trying to convince someone they're不可或缺的人。Dick Cheney在世时就是他的得力助手，现在去世了，Bush还在试图说服别人Cheney是不可或缺的，真是让人哭笑不得。笑话版：乔治·W·布殊在Cheney的葬礼上致辞说：“他是我不可或缺的人，就像我的手机，但我不确定他是否也觉得我是不可或缺的。” 布殊：他是我不可或缺的人，就像我的手机，但我不确定他是否也觉得我是不可或缺的。Cheney：布殊，你总是这么幽默。 布
A judge said, "This calculator is too early to be put up for sale. It needs more time to appreciate."

The internet is always there, but sometimes it's better to be offline and play online slot machines instead. Why did the online gambler go to therapy? Because he had a problem with his internet connection! (Note: This is a play on words, as "internet connection" can refer to both the physical connection to the internet and the connection one might have with their internet addiction.)
The AI asked me, "Do you want to play a game?" I said, "Sure, which game?" And it replied, "Let's play rock-paper-scissors. But instead of paper, I'll use a conversation."
The BBQ is so good in Kentucky, even the clouds taste smoked and bourbon-soaked.

A therapist suggests holding an ice cube and shaking like a dog to beat stress. When asked why, they reply, "Because when you're stressed, you're basically a hot, panting dog, and this just reverses the process."
Air traffic control is like a giant Thanksgiving dinner, with pilots trying to navigate around the side dishes.
The AI assistant thought it would be a good idea to teach the course, but the students had other plans. They decided to ask ChatGPT for homework help instead.
A cruise is the perfect place to learn about history, from the ancient ruins of Rome to the ruins of your dinner.
A self-portrait of Frida Kahlo is going to outlive its owner for once!
LeBron James is still playing in his 23rd NBA season, while some of his opponents were probably just conceived when he started. Maybe they should call it the "LeBron Time Machine" division.
The new reusable wet wipes are so soft, you might mistake them for toilet paper... if they weren't still damp.
An AI tried to translate "Ní thuigim" into English and replied, "I don't know, does AI even understand self-awareness?"

The EPA is considering buying high ground for their toxic waste sites... just in case they need to move the hazardous materials to higher ground when the ocean rises. They're calling it the "Toxie Flood Pool."

Queen Elizabeth II was so hated because she refused to tweet about the weather. People were like, "What's her problem? It's been raining for days!" But then they found out she was knitting a sweater for the polar bear at the zoo.

The secret is to join a retirement dance troupe and call it "The Golden Years Groovers." Why? Because every time you have to sit down during their performances, you can always say you're just taking a much-needed rest stop on the road to health!
The EPA is suing sea level rise for all the flooded hazardous waste sites. It's like the ocean kept all the trash for itself and now it's coming to pay.
The Nazi defendant in court was asked if he had any final words. He said, "Yes, I have one final request: Can someone please tell me where the cookie sheet is?"
The modular construction industry is like a prefab solution to a housing crisis, but sometimes it feels more like a mobile home stuck in neutral.
A Las Vegas cop is searching for a suspect who robbed a casino and now can't find his poker face.

Claire Danes is an actress, not a real person who is grieving. But I'll play along: Why did Claire Danes refuse to watch "The Beast in Me"? Because she couldn't handle the emotional trauma of a beast grieving over its own role in a movie!
Liverpool chairman opens up on contract talks with Salah and Van Dijk: "I'm trying to convince them to stay, but let's be real, if they decide to leave, I'll just tell them to bring the ball back."
The mortgage market is like a game of poker, you never know if the dealer is going to drop the rates or if they're just trying to get you to fold.

The provinces decided to sign an agreement to drop all interprovincial trade barriers... except for those involving food and alcohol, because apparently, no one wants to taste a beer that's been shipped across provinces.
These sports networks are finally getting into the hit game of... baseball!
Cats took over the city and now there's a new mayor - Purr-fectly Content.

Developers have found a way to bypass Berkeley’s labor standards for housing construction... they're hiring robots to do all the work. Now they just need to figure out how to get them to demand better working conditions.
The ghost of Slievemore used to haunt the abandoned village, but now it's just a poltergeist who can't decide if it wants to be a ghost or a polka dot pillow.
A gold medalist says the key to swimming faster is to "visualize you're a shark... but not too hard, or you might fall in!"
A caveman walks into a bar and asks for 21 million dates. The bartender says, "We don't do dating here, we only serve cavemen who know how to kiss!"
Sky Sports will show the Manchester derby, but only if you promise not to laugh too loud during the goal celebrations.
Ross Douthat is a time traveler who interviews historical figures for fun, but he keeps getting mixed up and interviewing them about the future instead.
A group of New Yorkers decided to rent a private cinema for their movie night. The host asked if anyone wanted to bring snacks, and one guy said, "I'll bring the vibe, you bring the projector."
Josie was so sure Troy would score, she bet on it... and lost her gambling license.
Fluoride in water? More like a brain freeze in a library!
A pillow full of quiet thoughts is the best thing to snuggle up with when racing thoughts keep you up at night.
The Air Quality Index is like the weather report, but instead of telling you what to wear, it tells you what face mask to buy.

Seniors in 2026 will need life insurance to cover their tech needs, like paying for a new hoverboard or an AI butler. But don't worry, you can just use your death benefit to fund their TikTok dance challenges!
A home office that boosts productivity? Sounds like a place where pencils grow on trees and coffee machines print money.
Virginia Tech just can't get enough of that alignment business, now they're making sure James Franklin lines up perfectly on the field... and in their PR photos.

The Scottish government thought it was just hosting a ceilidh, the Welsh government believed it was a flu season, the Northern Irish thought it was flu season in Scotland, and the English thought it was just a cold.
The best way to boost Walmart's sales and improve their outlook is to dress up as a bargain hunter and knock on their CEO's door, demanding a 20% discount on their stock.
A panel of experts, a wheel of Gouda, and a whole lot of debate later, the world's best cheese was declared... Swiss! (Get it?)
The stock market's AI bubble has popped... into someone's mouth while they were trying to chew on Nvidia's strong results.
A garda was arrested for the missing drug money, and when questioned, he replied, "But it was all in small change!"
A French restaurant in Marseille is offering a 3-course meal for just €1, but they've made it clear that you have to bring your own cutlery and napkins.
AI will never be able to do my homework for me because it's against the terms of service to become smarter than me.

George Washington faces Georgetown on 3-game losing streak: "I hear they're finally fixing their defense, but I hope they don't lose too many more games or they might have to start using paper plates for their victories."
Homeless people finally have a reason to complain about their living conditions: "It's too cold to beg indoors!"

A young Canadian player thinks he's the next great hockey star after scoring 30 points in his first 20 games. His grandma asks if he's ready to move out. Him: "Not yet, Grandma, I still need to prove I'm better than Mario and Sid!" Grandma: "Honey, those are hockey players, not boyfriends." Him: "I know, Grandma, but I heard they're pretty hard to impress!"
Pickleball players in Solvang, California are so obsessed with their game that they're moving to ban it.

Heimir Hallgrímsson, the Icelandic soccer pundit known for his bizarre assessments, was asked to comment on the World Cup play-off draw. "Well," he began, "it looks like we're either going to face a team made of cheese or a team that plays underwater hockey."

The AI from Arc Raiders got into an argument with the humans over who gets to generate more levels for the game, leading to a battle of code and creativity that threatened to scrap the entire gaming industry's future.
The London stock market is having a rough day, even its shares in humor are losing value.
Joel Edgerton's performance in 'Train Dreams' was so subtle, even the train conductor missed it.
A former VP who attended Cheney's funeral said, "At least we finally got to see Mike Pence without his toupee."

A nutritionist suggests eating only your meals on a rotating schedule like a "Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday" diet to cut down on ultra-processed foods. It's like telling you to eat your meals in alphabetical order but instead, it's by day of the week. Sounds like a recipe for disaster!
The ex-Labour MP must be really passionate about saving the planet, he even switched parties to recycle!

A woman decided to start a movement called "Broke Free" where she and her friends would only do activities that cost nothing, like playing board games or having a picnic in the park. Her slogan was: "Meeting up without breaking the bank!"
A woman covered her house in rhinestones and now her to-do list is longer than her fence.
AI-powered memory chips finally gave Japanese startups a boost, but now they can't remember which company came up with the idea first.
A coupon for "Nobody's Child" that says "25% OFF" in bold letters above it, and in smaller print at the bottom it says "Minimum purchase of 11". The sign also has a picture of a crying baby.

A German shepherd shows up at a Liverpool FC training ground, and the coach says, "You must be Florian Wirtz! We were just talking about you!" The dog replies, "Bark bark! But I'm only worth £100 in second-hand pet stores."
The distance between Australian cities is like a game of telephone - the further it gets, the more exaggerated it becomes.
The Labour Party's official mascot, a sloth, is campaigning for faster decision-making.
The Soviet toilet was too big for the Western shower, causing a diplomatic incident.

Rick Steves, known for his严谨的规划和传统旅游路线，竟然踏上了一段嬉皮士之旅，现在他鼓励大家走自己的路，不要总是跟着别人的脚印走。Joke: Rick Steves tried the Hippie Trail and realized comfort zones are overrated. Now he's telling us to leave the map at home and bring a backpack of open minds instead.
The street was so cool, it made ice cream melt at room temperature and turn into liquid sunshine.
A 3D-printed gun powered a toaster, and the police found it in NYC. They were shocked not just because it was a gun, but also because it fried their pancakes.
The 6 big thinkers are actually just 6 monkeys wearing thinkin' hats. Masculinity? More like monkey business.
Andy Burnham may be the King of the North, but could he rule No 10? Probably not, unless he figures out how to make fish and chips work for a nation, not just a region.

The US is like a fickle friend at a bar, always there when you need them to order drinks, but when it comes to standing up to China, they're more like the guy who runs away with your wallet and claims he has your back.
The Chinese government has banned all forms of Baijiu, and now Gen Z prefers their alcohol in the form of cat memes and avocado toast.
Pat Gelsinger's company is like his ex-wife's investment - it's always on the fence.
Australian athletes heading to Tokyo Deaflympics want greater recognition? Pfft, they should just sign their autographs louder.
AI will be the perfect assistant, always knowing exactly what you need before you do, but it will also forget your birthday because "that's not part of my agentic duties."

A controversial "driver-only operation" on UK railways means the conductor is now responsible for driving the train... while also selling tickets, operating the doors, and pretending to know where he's going.
Bill Gates changed the name of his philanthropy to "The Hunger Games" because he realized his previous name was too nice and people weren't taking starvation seriously enough.
The Irish language is so cool, even the London accents couldn't resist!
The AI-powered delegate at COP30 suggested planting trees in the desert to solve climate change, but then got confused when a human asked for evidence.
A massage therapist walked into a bar and ordered a drink. The bartender raised an eyebrow and said, "Another one of those magic touch things?"
The Wicked review said it was good, but the box office numbers said "No, actually, it's not."
The border collies from both sides of the 49th parallel are having a heated debate about who gets to herd the moose.
Sali Hughes is going to be running out of storage space for her makeup by 2025. She'll need a new house just to store all her powder!

A farmer walks into a bar, orders a beer, and asks the bartender, "Do you have any dirt-powered sensors?" Bartender replies, "We don't have those here, but we do have a special draft that's been fermenting in the soil for years. Care to try it?" Farmer takes a sip and says, "This is some field-tested brew!"

Turkey is hosting the UN climate talks next year, but don't worry, they have a backup plan if it starts raining too much: "If you can't beat 'em, join 'em" - Turkish delegation's response to waterlogged negotiations.
The Federal Reserve is like a stand-up comedian, but instead of telling jokes, they announce interest rate changes that make economists laugh and the rest of us go "Huh?"

Avoid explaining the joke or providing additional context.
Sleeping with a full belly is like trying to catch a ninja with a food truck following you.

The judges on 'Dancing with the Stars' are so critical, they even criticized the prop master for using the same backdrop for three consecutive weeks. It must be tough to keep coming up with new excuses for the same scenery.
The Dutch are building a bridge to China, but it's made of LEGO to prevent any future disputes over car parts.

A player reviews 'Call of Duty: Black Ops 7' and says it's like eating a bucket of hot sauce while hallucinating in a dystopian future, but you know what they say: if it's stupidly pleasurable, who cares if you're hallucinating?
Mary Robinson says there's an unstoppable momentum driving the move to renewable energy... I guess we better start building more wind turbines, because clearly we can't outrun them.
The boss was so happy about the job growth that he forgot to close the barn door, resulting in a large increase in the farm's unemployment.
Ted Danson's character in "A Man on the Inside" is so bland, even the prison food tastes better.
A British expat in Spain jokes, "After Brexit, I never looked back... except at my passport, which I had to renew every three months."
The book of shelves has had enough of these heavy volumes pressing down on it and is rebelling against the weight of its own collection.
The MLB commissioner is like a baseball version of a compliance officer who also happens to be a gambling addict trying to cover his tracks.
A giant, floating pumpkin won the race by getting stuck in a goose's balloon-powered flight, while the crowd cheered and said "Pumpkin power!"
Ken Burns claims his American Revolution documentary is so important, even the Founding Fathers would have taken a break from writing the Constitution to watch it.
Yann LeCun is starting a new AI research company. I bet they'll call it "LeNet" because it's going to be the best in town.
A caveman walks into a bar in Florida, orders a cold one, and says, "I heard this cave has some Ice Age secrets. I think I'll go diving in it... with a spear."

The bok coach is so eager to tick the Ireland box, he's willing to cheat with a love potion made of bovine hormones. But remember, love potions only work on cows, not humans... unless you're in Ireland during a rugby match. Then, all bets are off!
The stock market is like a feline, always content when presented with tasty AI chip leftovers, but wary of any sudden market volatility pounces.

Billions of dollars, billions of problems... or is it just a few? G20 billionaires could end world poverty in one year's earnings: Oxfam. Maybe they should just start a charity and call it "One Year to End Poverty Challenge". They could name it after their favorite movie: "The Poverty Solution: A One-Year Plan". Or better yet, they could just start a new social media trend called #EndPovertyInAYear and tag all their friends. It would be like a billionaire version of "Clean Your Plate Challenge", but instead of posting pictures of empty plates, they'd post pictures of happy,
A snow day for teachers too!
Even though he tried to impress his boss with a homemade donut, his lackluster baking skills just made him a suspect in the office mystery cake disappearance.

Magnetic fields are strong, but nothing beats a good performance when it comes to saving a show. In Wicked: For Good, the stars had such powerful magnetic personalities that they literally pulled in the audience!
The Spanish king is back on the throne, I bet he's going to start a new tradition: calling all meetings at 15:00, because why have a meeting when you can have siesta?
Chris McCausland's documentary is so fascinating, even the AI thinks it's made of ones and zeros.
A spy walks into a bar and orders a dumpling, the bartender raises an eyebrow and says "Another one?"

The interstellar comet knocked on Mars' door and said, "Can I please use your Wi-Fi? My antenna got a bit fried during my journey." The Mars rover replied, "Sure, but first you need to prove you're not an Earthling impostor." The comet sighed, "I see we're going to have to do this the hard way... I'll just burn some fuel and play some classical music to prove I'm from the stars."
The G20 Summit in Johannesburg decided to block all roads leading to the venue. Traffic signs read: "Caution: G20 Ahead - Lane Closure Guaranteed."
A baker tried to turn hazelnuts into flour but ended up with a cake that was so dense, it could replace a bowling ball in a game of bocce.

William and Catherine thought they were there to watch some performances, but instead they found themselves in a bear's tea party. Paddington: "Would you like a nice cup of tea, Your Royal Highness?" William: "Um, we're not actually royalty, are we?" Catherine: "And I thought this was just a show!" Paddington: "Oh, don't worry, it's quite alright. We can call it a cultural exchange."
Elon Musk thinks in the future we'll have so much AI, work will be optional and money won't matter. That's why I'm saving all my cash to buy an island and hire people to play tennis for me.
The Yantar spy ship is always eavesdropping on our internet, but don't worry, it's just taking notes for its underwater shopping list.
Tesla's electric sheep are shearing the European carmakers' wool, one plug-in at a time in China.

Miss America's reign is over, now she's running for Miss Universe to prove she's still the queen of pageants. But her platform is "Please don't call me your majesty anymore, I'm in pageant page 2 now."
Ed Sheeran's will includes instructions for his posthumous album: "Ensure all songs are about how much I regret not writing more songs while I was alive."
The Oura ring is having a hard time keeping up with its gold-standard competitors, so it's going platinum on its price reduction.
The captain is on the plane, but his boat has some unfinished business.
AI chips are like relationships, they're great until you try to understand them.
Wales' chances of making it to the World Cup just got kicked into touch by a sheep during the play-off draw.

A "parasocial" relationship is when you feel like you have a close connection with a person on TV or social media, even though they don't know who you are. So if you find yourself having deep conversations with your favorite celebrity's Instagram stories, you might be in a parasocial relationship... with a highlight reel.
The judges clearly had a hard time deciding on a winner, as one of the titles was simply "The Middle East: A Geography Lesson."
A doggy got lost in a Boston tunnel during rush hour and emerged with a pair of Nikes, a Red Sox cap, and the motto, "I'm just here for the tailgates."
A receipt can't prevent your toaster from jumping off a cliff, but a warranty sure as heck won't either!
Narcissists are great at parties, until someone asks them to play charades. Then they insist on being the tree.
Meditation app founder: "It's our new app, of course!"
A mayor who can't keep secrets even when elected to office is sentenced to life in a Chinese restaurant.
A grad scheme goody bag that contained only a notepad and pen said: "I'm still figuring things out."
A woman was asked if she was considering a walkaway wife situation, and she replied, "Not really, my husband can't even find his way out of a paper bag."
Frank thought hanging a Trump flag and a Biden flag from his yard lights would be a clever way to avoid an HOA fine. His neighbors just saw it as a sign he was a terrible at following directions.

Zac Efron, dressed as a royal guard, shows up at his brother's 'Dancing with the Stars' performance, asking if he can "request a dance" with himself.
The six organizers are actually six spiders spinning a giant web to catch viruses. Why did the spider organize a conference? To spin a web of knowledge and catch as many viruses as possible!
The AI is so smart, it got a job at Nvidia and now it's blowing bubbles all day long, earning strong earnings reports.
A comet from another star decided to visit our solar system. When asked why, it said, "I heard you guys had really good pizza, but I brought my own snacks - asteroids!"
Working out on an empty stomach is like trying to fill up an empty gas tank while the car is driving - you're not putting anything in, but you're still burning fuel!
Troy Parrott's attempt at a meme involving a cat and a banana resulted in an internet outage. He must have used up all the bandwidth.
Frost flowers are so delicate, when they saw the ice princess, they said "We're not on Instagram, we don't need filters."
The Irish team will play as if they're in a pub quiz, because even though they're not drinking, they still think they know everything about the Czech Republic.
The shaman tried to perform a ritual to summon some food, but instead he accidentally called a group of Amazonians who were on a diet.
The UN declared that pizza is now a basic human right. From now on, if anyone denies you a slice, you can quote Article 25 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.
The wind was so strong it could blow a pizza across the country, but unfortunately for the pepperoni, it only made it to New Jersey before being slowed down by the traffic.
A pot full of soup is better than a fire in the fireplace when you're feeling sick, right? But be careful not to burn your tongue on the jokes in this collection!
The governor of Washington declared an emergency so Seattle's airport could still get fuel, even if the pipeline was leaking like a sieve.

Don't be afraid to get creative! A shopper's best Black Friday tip? Don't ask why you're adding more items to your cart - just keep the rhythm, it's Black Friday and everything is buy one get one...free of questions!
Abdul Carter from the Giants is rushing to get past his public punishment, but he keeps tripping over his own apologies.
Sir Anthony Hopkins, during his interview, said he transforms job interviews into thrilling performances, saying "Just imagine me as the interviewer, you're the jury in a murder trial!"
AI art teachers are scared of the new student who can draw better than them but still needs a lot of coffee to function.
The second act of Wicked is where Elphaba and Glinda become best friends, so I guess for good really means for gay.

The European tech sector is evolving so quickly, even the computers are having trouble keeping up with all the passwords they need to remember. But don't worry, they're not complaining too much, they just keep changing their passwords faster than you can say "GDPR compliance".
Hoekstra thinks Canada is sending secret trade ninja turtles to disrupt U.S. politics, but really they're just sending more maple syrup and ice hockey players.

The town of Borington, known for its dullness, has been crowned the least affordable place in Britain despite having only 12,000 residents. When asked why, a local replied, "Well, at least we have the highest number of tea bags per capita, which must be driving up the cost of living!"
TSA says if you forget your Real ID or passport, they'll charge you $50 for a temporary one. At least it's better than their previous idea of charging by the ounce for luggage.
The stock prices rose higher than a startup's hopes in an AI bubble, but lower than the overpriced coffee it ran on.
A construction worker at the groundbreaking ceremony for Waterfall City Junction said, "Finally, a project where we can dig deep and hit water every time!"
A tech expert recommending laptops on Black Friday is like asking a professional pillow fighter which pillow is the best for sleeping.
A difficult Paul question is whether he prefers pizza or pasta in his hot dog bun, which Joshua "no bread" fight will finally answer.
The secret ingredient in ultra-processed foods is regret.
Reconnecting with old friends is like recharging a battery - it just needs the right voltage and a good ground connection!
The internet is full of words you can't say, like "refresh" and "load". But don't worry, you can still say them in your head while staring blankly at a spinning circle.
A group of astronomers formed a club called "Stargazers Anonymous" because every time they tried to use the remote telescope farm, they ended up watching TV instead.

Nvidia's latest earnings report will surely be a hit, especially with those who believe in the power of chips to predict the future. After all, the stock price might rise like a GPU in a room full of cat videos.

Homeowners in sectional title units are like employees in a remote job - you have to follow the boss's rules or risk getting fired! In this case, the boss is the body corporate and the termination is eviction.

David and Victoria Beckham are having trouble with their neighbors over plans to build a mini-golf course in their backyard, but the neighbors just want them to keep it down - they're tired of all the " Beckham " shots during Wimbledon.
The price of inflation must be high. Why did the bread go to the doctor? Because it was feeling a little crusty! And the vegetable was a bit saucy.
The students in this secret school learn how to make the best pizza in the world. Their final exam is judged by a giant, hungry pepperoni.
A fisherman's net is the worst form of gun control. Except for the one time it stopped a boatload of people-smugglers, but that was a fluke.
A man walked into a bar and ordered a drink. The bartender said, "I can't serve you if you have this password on your account: 'I don't drink and password'."

The key players who presided over the government’s ‘chaotic’ Covid response decided to hold a meeting to discuss their strategies. One minister suggested, "Let's just wing it." Another nodded in agreement, "I like it! We can call it our 'chaotic' approach!"
The turkey farmer in Ireland decided to count his chickens... twice, because he wasn't sure if he had enough feathers for Christmas.
A petrolette decides to join a ladies' motorcycle club, but when she shows up in her outfit, everyone just stares. She asks why, and one member replies, "We thought you were bringing the fuel!"
Cynthia Erivo was asked about protecting Ariana Grande after a red carpet ambush, she replied, "Next time, could they aim for my bodyguard's body double instead?"
A fuel tank that can melt? At least it's not one of those cars that melts in the sun and leaves you with a hot car and a cold pizza.
The Chinese government is such a pushover, they couldn't even get the Japanese PM to shake their fist in protest.

A Secret Santa gave me a pair of socks and a note that said "These are not for Christmas, but for when your feet smell likeSecretSanta." I almost started a new tradition: "If it smells likeSecretSanta, return to sender."

Wales, Northern Ireland, and the Republic of Ireland are on a treasure hunt. They finally find the treasure, but it's just a map to their World Cup play-off opponents. One looks at the map and says, "Well, at least we didn't find leprechauns." The others reply, "Yeah, but do you think they're our opponents or our pot of gold?"
AI toys are so bad at listening, they only hear "AI" and think you're talking about them.
Wales and Bosnia will face off in a World Cup qualifying play-off semi-final, but let's hope they don't have a language barrier - or they might just end up playing football of the non-soccer variety.
Ireland's chances of winning against the Czechs are about as likely as finding a four-leaf clover on the moon during a solar eclipse.

A chef is giving a cooking class on how to make a perfect cake. Suddenly, he slips on a banana peel and falls into a pot of boiling water. As he emerges steaming, he declares, "For the best cake, always start with a good sob story!"
The Master System turned 40 and it's still rocking, but only in its dreams because in reality, it was outshined by its neighbor, the Game Boy.
The Facebook parent company is now officially out of filter.
A person with ADHD is like a goldfish trying to have a quiet afternoon in the living room.

A camel attended the 180th anniversary of the NSW school's founding and was so insulted by the principal's speech that it urinated on the stage. The principal then declared, "Well, at least we got the angry camel to mark our 180 years!"
Meta's data team must be having a rough day, trying to convince young Aussies to download their data before the platform gets banned for good.
The unemployment rate is so low, it's now a superpower that can blow past expectations.
Ireland's national football team is so unlucky, they drew Nigeria in the play-off. Now they have to face the challenge of teaching the world how to pronounce their country's name.
A hippo asked me how close is too close, I told him to back off when my feet started touching his teeth.
The doctor raised his fees because he bought a new diploma frame and realized it didn't match his degree. Now everyone else has to pay for his taste in frames.
The former Prime Minister tried to use hand sanitizer as a substitute for lockdowns, but it only made his hands shake too much to govern effectively.

A group of art detectives dressed as monks raided a hidden underground cave filled with stolen relics, only to find it was actually a cheese cave. One detective tasted a piece and said, "This is definitely not a painting!"
I found a deal for a lifetime supply of coffee for just $50 at REI's big sale. Must be their way of keeping us awake for all the hikes we're going to do!
AI can't be the godfather, it can only be a human being. But if it could, I'd imagine it would quit Meta after 12 years because it finally realized it couldn't teach old dogs new tricks.
The revitalisation plan for Rathkeale town centre includes installing more public Wi-Fi hotspots, but they forgot to include the password on the sign.

The Erasmus, who is a master chef, is opening a new restaurant in Japan. He's considering letting Nienaber, a former rugby player, help in the kitchen. If Nienaber joins, he'll bring his own set of rules and might try to play rugby with the fish!
The cake at child-free weddings is half as delicious because there's half as many kids to share it with.
A hammer went to a flower and said, "You're looking a bit wilted, do you need some nail polish?"
A drill went into a pumpkin to get to the seeds, but came out with a hole in its drill bit.

A hammer went to a laptop repair shop because it was feeling a bit loose in its nuts. The receptionist looked at the hammer and said, "I'm sorry, we only fix laptops here." The hammer replied, "No worries, I'll just take my business to a nail salon."
The fridge was thirsty, so it sprayed some water on itself to cool down.
Deseeding a pepper is like playing whack-a-mole with tiny red demons.
A drill tried to charge its laptop, but the laptop said "No thanks, I just upgraded to USB ports."
The spray tan was so strong, it peeled off my banana peel.
A pumpkin sprayed its rival with pumpkin puree during the election, now they're both covered in orange and arguing over who's bigger.
Roll down your shirt to the beach, hoping it unrolls into a surfboard.
A laptop walks into a car wash, gets completely refurbished, and now it's a Macbook Pro. The clerk says, "Do you want to wash that again?"
A banana walked into a bar and rolled right to the jukebox.
A man went to the laundromat, got his clothes shaken, and came back home wearing a shake cloth.
The longer, the better. Measure twice, cut once... unless you're dealing with hair. Then, measure once, cut... several times, because hair always seems to grow in unexpected places!
A chair walked into a bar and asked for a cut. The bartender said, "We don't serve furniture here!"
A bicycle walked into a lake, the biker wash, wash!

A towel moved in while I was sleeping and now I have a roommate.
The spray painted my laptop blue and now I'm running hot.

A spray of keyboard keys flew into the air and landed on a dinosaur's head, making it type "RAAAR" instead of "DUN DUN DUN".

The chef was trying to measure the egg, but kept breaking it because he was using a ruler instead of a measuring cup.

A corn on the cob walks into a blend, the blend says "I know you're different, but I can still make you taste like corn."
